  "english": [
    "The <b>Rabbi Yitzhak ben Aḥa</b> mentioned in a ruling <b>of <i>halakha</i> is</b> the same as the <b>Rabbi Yitzḥak ben Pineḥas</b> who appears in statements <b>of <i>aggada</i>. And your mnemonic</b> to remember the names is the standard phrase: <b>Listen my brothers and friends [<i>shimu na aḥai vere’ai</i>].</b> <i>Shimu</i> sounds like <i>shema’ta</i>, the term for <i>halakha</i>, while <i>aḥai</i> is similar to the patronymic ben Aḥa.",
    "<b>Rabba bar bar Ḥana said</b> that <b>Rabbi Yoḥanan said, citing Rabbi Yehuda, son of Rabbi Elai: Eat an onion [<i>batzal</i>] and sit in the shade [<i>batzel</i>],</b> i.e., eat inexpensive food while sitting in a comfortable place, <b>but do not eat</b> expensive <b>geese and chickens, as your heart will pursue you,</b> i.e., you will develop a taste for luxuries. Devote <b>less to your food and your drink and</b> spend <b>more on your house,</b> as one’s house is a better investment than food.",
    "<b>When Ulla came</b> from Eretz Yisrael to Babylonia <b>he said</b> that <b>they say</b> the following <b>proverb in the west,</b> Eretz Yisrael: <b>One who eats a fat tail [<i>alita</i>] must hide in the attic [<i>aliyata</i>]</b> from creditors who think he is wealthy. <b>One who eats vegetables [<i>kakulei</i>] can lie down in the city’s garbage [<i>kiklei</i>]</b> without fear of others, as he is not in debt.",
    "<strong>MISHNA:</strong> The <i>tanna</i> describes the beginning of the Passover seder. The attendants <b>poured</b> the wine of <b>the first cup</b> for the leader of the seder. <b>Beit Shammai say: One recites the blessing over the</b> sanctification of the <b>day,</b> i.e., the <i>kiddush</i> for the Festival: Who blesses Israel and the Festivals, <b>and thereafter he recites the blessing over the wine:</b> Who creates fruit of the vine. <b>And Beit Hillel say: One recites the blessing over the wine and thereafter recites the blessing over the day.</b>",
    "<strong>GEMARA:</strong> <b>The Sages taught</b> in the <i>Tosefta</i>: These are the <b>matters</b> of dispute <b>between Beit Shammai and Beit Hillel with regard to</b> the <i>halakhot</i> of <b>a meal. Beit Shammai say:</b> When reciting <i>kiddush</i> over wine, <b>one recites a blessing over the</b> sanctification of the <b>day and thereafter recites a blessing over the wine, because the day causes the wine to come</b> before the meal. And Beit Shammai offer an additional reason. <b>The day has</b> already <b>been sanctified and the wine has not yet come.</b>",
    "<b>And Beit Hillel say: One recites the blessing over the wine and thereafter recites a blessing over the day, because the wine causes <i>kiddush</i> to be recited.</b> Since one does not recite <i>kiddush</i> without wine or bread, clearly the wine is the primary feature of the ritual. <b>Alternatively, the blessing over wine is</b> recited <b>frequently and the blessing over the day is not</b> recited <b>frequently,</b> and there is a general principle: When <b>a frequent</b> practice <b>and an infrequent</b> practice coincide, <b>the frequent</b> practice <b>takes precedence</b> over the infrequent practice. The <i>Tosefta</i> concludes: <b>And</b> the <b><i>halakha</i></b> is <b>in accordance with the statement of Beit Hillel.</b>",
    "The Gemara asks: <b>What is alternatively?</b> Why did Beit Hillel cite an additional reason? The Gemara explains: <b>And if you say</b> that <b>there</b> Beit Shammai cite <b>two</b> reasons, <b>and here</b> Beit Hillel offer only <b>one;</b> therefore, Beit Hillel said <b>they are two</b> reasons here too: When <b>a frequent</b> practice <b>and an infrequent</b> practice coincide, <b>the frequent</b> practice <b>takes precedence</b> over the infrequent practice.",
    "It was taught in the <i>Tosefta</i>: <b>And</b> the <b><i>halakha</i></b> is <b>in accordance with the statement of Beit Hillel.</b> The Gemara comments: It is <b>obvious</b> that this is so, <b>as a Divine Voice emerged</b> and proclaimed that the <i>halakha</i> is always in accordance with the opinion of Beit Hillel. Why was it necessary for the <i>Tosefta</i> to state that in this particular case the <i>halakha</i> is in accordance with their opinion? The Gemara answers: <b>If you wish, say</b> that this <i>Tosefta</i> was taught <b>before the Divine Voice</b> emerged and proclaimed that principle.",
    "And <b>if you wish, say</b> instead that this statement was indeed issued <b>after the Divine Voice</b> emerged, and the <i>Tosefta</i> is in accordance with the opinion of <b>Rabbi Yehoshua, who said</b> that <b>one disregards a Divine Voice</b> when deciding <i>halakha</i>. Just as Rabbi Yehoshua disregarded the Divine Voice in his dispute with Rabbi Eliezer, so too, one disregards the Divine Voice that proclaimed that the <i>halakha</i> is in accordance with the opinion of Beit Hillel. Therefore, it was necessary to state that the <i>halakha</i> is in fact in accordance with the opinion of Beit Hillel here.",
    "<strong>MISHNA:</strong> The attendants <b>brought</b> vegetables <b>before</b> the leader of the seder prior to the meal, if there were no other vegetables on the table. <b>He dips the <i>ḥazeret</i></b> into water or vinegar, to taste some food <b>before he reaches the</b> dessert of <b>the bread,</b> i.e., the bitter herbs, which were eaten after the <i>matza</i>. <b>They brought before him <i>matza</i> and</b> <i>ḥazeret</i> <b>and <i>ḥaroset</i>, and</b> at least <b>two cooked dishes</b> in honor of the Festival. The <i>tanna</i> comments that this was the practice, <b>although</b> eating <b><i>ḥaroset</i> is not a mitzva</b> but merely a custom. <b>Rabbi Eliezer ben Tzadok says:</b> Actually, it is <b>a mitzva</b> to eat <i>ḥaroset</i>. <b>And in</b> the period when <b>the Temple</b> stood and they offered the Paschal lamb, <b>they brought before him the body of the Paschal lamb.</b>"
  ],
  "gemara": [
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sentence\" id=\"0\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>רַבִּי יִצְחָק בֶּן אַחָא דִּשְׁמַעְתָּא, הוּא רַבִּי יִצְחָק",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "בֶּן פִּנְחָס דְּאַגָּדְתָּא. וְסִימָנָיךְ (שִׁמְעוּ נָא אַחַיי",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְרֵעַיי). <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"1\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>אָמַר רָבָא בַּר בַּר חָנָה אָמַר רַבִּי יוֹחָנָן מִשְּׁמֵיהּ",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "דְּרַבִּי יְהוּדָה בְּרַבִּי אִילְעַי: אֱכוֹל בָּצָל וְשֵׁב בַּצֵּל,",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְלָא תֵּיכוּל אֲווֹזִין וְתַרְנְגוֹלִין וִיהֵא לִבְּךָ רוֹדֵף",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "עָלֶיךָ. פְּחוֹת מִמֵּיכְלָךְ וּמִמִּשְׁתְּיָךְ, וְתוֹסֵיף עַל",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "דֵּירְתָךְ. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"2\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>כִּי אֲתָא עוּלָּא, אָמַר: מַתְלָא מָתְלִין",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "בְּמַעְרְבָא דְּאָכֵיל אַלְיְתָא — טָשֵׁי בְּעִלִּיתָא.",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "דְּאָכֵיל קָקוּלִי — אַקִּיקְלֵי דְמָתָא שָׁכֵיב.",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sentence\" id=\"3\" type=\"start\">&star;</span><big><strong>מַתְנִי׳</strong></big> מָזְגוּ לוֹ כּוֹס רִאשׁוֹן. בֵּית שַׁמַּאי אוֹמְרִים:",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מְבָרֵךְ עַל הַיּוֹם, וְאַחַר כָּךְ מְבָרֵךְ עַל הַיַּיִן. וּבֵית",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "הִלֵּל אוֹמְרִים: מְבָרֵךְ עַל הַיַּיִן, וְאַחַר כָּךְ",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מְבָרֵךְ עַל הַיּוֹם. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"4\" type=\"start\">&star;</span><big><strong>גְּמָ׳</strong></big> תָּנוּ רַבָּנַן: דְּבָרִים שֶׁבֵּין בֵּית שַׁמַּאי וּבֵית",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "הִלֵּל בַּסְּעוּדָה. בֵּית שַׁמַּאי אוֹמְרִים: מְבָרֵךְ עַל הַיּוֹם, וְאַחַר",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "כָּךְ מְבָרֵךְ עַל הַיַּיִן — מִפְּנֵי שֶׁהַיּוֹם גּוֹרֵם לַיַּיִן",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "שֶׁיָּבֹא, וּכְבָר קִידֵּשׁ הַיּוֹם וַעֲדַיִין יַיִן לֹא בָּא. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"5\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>וּבֵית הִלֵּל",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אוֹמְרִים: מְבָרֵךְ עַל הַיַּיִן, וְאַחַר כָּךְ מְבָרֵךְ עַל הַיּוֹם —",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מִפְּנֵי שֶׁהַיַּיִן גּוֹרֵם לְקִידּוּשׁ שֶׁתֵּאָמֵר.",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "דָּבָר אַחֵר: בִּרְכַּת הַיַּיִן תְּדִירָה וּבִרְכַּת הַיּוֹם",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אֵינָהּ תְּדִירָה. תָּדִיר וְשֶׁאֵינוֹ תָּדִיר — תָּדִיר קוֹדֵם.",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְהִילְכְתָא כְּדִבְרֵי בֵּית הִלֵּל. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"6\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>מַאי דָּבָר אַחֵר? וְכִי תֵּימָא הָתָם",
      "segment_ids": [
        6
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "תַּרְתֵּי וְהָכָא חֲדָא — הָכָא נָמֵי תַּרְתֵּי נִינְהוּ: תָּדִיר",
      "segment_ids": [
        6
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְשֶׁאֵינוֹ תָּדִיר — תָּדִיר קוֹדֵם. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"7\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>וַהֲלָכָה כְּדִבְרֵי בֵּית הִלֵּל:",
      "segment_ids": [
        7
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "פְּשִׁיטָא, דְּהָא נְפַיק בַּת קוֹל! אִיבָּעֵית אֵימָא:",
      "segment_ids": [
        7
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "קוֹדֶם בַּת קוֹל, <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"8\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>וְאִי בָּעֵית אֵימָא: לְאַחַר בַּת קוֹל,",
      "segment_ids": [
        8
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְרַבִּי יְהוֹשֻׁעַ הִיא, דְּאָמַר: אֵין מַשְׁגִּיחִין בְּבַת",
      "segment_ids": [
        8
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "קוֹל. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"9\" type=\"start\">&star;</span><big><strong>מַתְנִי׳</strong></big> הֵבִיאוּ לְפָנָיו, מְטַבֵּל בַּחֲזֶרֶת",
      "segment_ids": [
        9
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "עַד שֶׁמַּגִּיעַ לְפַרְפֶּרֶת הַפַּת. הֵבִיאוּ לְפָנָיו",
      "segment_ids": [
        9
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מַצָּה וַחֲזֶרֶת וַחֲרוֹסֶת וּשְׁנֵי תַבְשִׁילִין, אַף עַל פִּי שֶׁאֵין",
      "segment_ids": [
        9
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "חֲרוֹסֶת מִצְוָה. רַבִּי אֱלִיעֶזֶר (בֶּן) צָדוֹק אוֹמֵר: מִצְוָה.",
      "segment_ids": [
        9
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וּבְמִקְדָּשׁ הָיוּ מְבִיאִין לְפָנָיו גּוּפוֹ שֶׁל פֶּסַח.",
      "segment_ids": [
        9
      ]
    }
  ],
  "rashi": [
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>רַבִּי יִצְחָק בֶּן אַחָא דִּשְׁמַעְתָּא.</b> רבי יצחק סתם האמור באגדתא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "ר' יצחק בן פנחס הוא: <b>שמעו</b> <b>נא</b> <b>אחיי.</b> דשמעתא בן אחא: <b>ולבך</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>רודף</b> <b>עליך.</b> מתאוה לאכול כל שעה שהורגלת: <b>קקולי.</b> ירקות:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>אַקִּיקְלֵי דְמָתָא.</b> על אשפות העיר מקום ששאר בני העיר יושבין",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:3:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "הואיל ואין תובעין לו כלום:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:3:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>כָּךְ מְבָרֵךְ עַל הַיַּיִן.</b> וה\"ה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "למקדש על הפת: <b>גמ'</b> <b>שהיין</b> <b>גורם</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>לקידוש</b> <b>שתיאמר.</b> שאם אין לו יין",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "או פת אינו מקדש: <b>מתני'</b> <b>הביאו</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>לפניו.</b> ירקות: <b>מטבל</b> <b>בחזרת.</b> זהו",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "לשון הגמרא כדתניא לעיל (<a href=\"/pesachim/107b\">פסחים דף קז:</a>)",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "השמש מטבל בבני מעים לפי שכל",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "מאכלם ע\"י טיבול: <b>מטבל</b> <b>בחזרת.</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "כלומר אם אין שם ירק אחר מטבל",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "החזרת בחרוסת ואוכל: <b>עד</b> <b>שמגיע</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>לפרפרת</b> <b>הפת.</b> קודם שיגיע לאותה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "חזרת שהוא אוכל אחר המצה שהוא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "מברך עליה על אכילת מרור וטיבול",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "ראשון כדי שיכיר תינוק וישאל לפי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "שאין רגילין בני אדם לאכול ירק קודם",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "סעודה: <b>הביאו</b> <b>לפניו.</b> אחר אותו",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "טיבול: <b>מצה</b> <b>מרור</b> <b>וחרוסת</b> <b>ושני</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>תבשילין</b> <b>ואף</b> <b>על</b> <b>פי</b> <b>שאין</b> <b>החרוסת</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>מצוה.</b> ולקמיה פריך הואיל ולאו",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "מצוה אמאי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 114a:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
